text.section:
Before a license expires, the holder of the license periodically may renew it for an additional 2-year term, if the holder:
otherwise is entitled to a license;
files with the Commissioner a renewal application on the form that the Commissioner provides;
pays to the Commissioner the renewal fee required by § 2-112 of this article;
is in compliance with the bond requirement of § 10-206 of this subtitle; and
if the Commissioner determines that an examination is advisable to determine the trustworthiness or competence of a holder, passes an examination given by the Commissioner.
